18 (a) (1) IN THIS SECTION, “HATE BIAS INCIDENT” MEANS AN ACT OF
19 HOSTILITY OR AGGRESSION THAT:
20 (I) IS DIRECTED AT AN INDIVIDUAL OR A GROUP, PRIVATE
21 PROPERTY, OR PUBLIC PROPERTY;
22 (II) IS MOTIVATED, IN WHOLE OR SUBSTANTIALLY IN PART, BY
23 ANOTHER INDIVIDUAL’S OR GROUP’S ACTUAL OR PERCEIVED PROTECTED CLASS
24 STATUS AS SPECIFIED IN SUBSECTION (C)(1) OF THIS SECTION; AND
25 (III) DOES NOT CONSTITUTE A CRIME UNDER STATE OR FEDERAL
26 LAW.
27 (2) “HATE BIAS INCIDENT” INCLUDES:
28 (I) SLURS, NAME–CALLING, AND INSULTS;

