1 (II) THE DISPLAY OF MATERIAL WITH OFFENSIVE LANGUAGE,
2 SYMBOLS, OR THREATS TARGETING A PROTECTED CLASS ON PRIVATE PROPERTY;
3 (III) THE POSTING OF MATERIAL WITH OFFENSIVE LANGUAGE,
4 SYMBOLS, OR THREATS TARGETING A PROTECTED CLASS THAT DOES NOT RESULT
5 IN PROPERTY DAMAGE;
6 (IV) ELECTRONIC AND ONLINE DISTRIBUTION OF MATERIAL
7 WITH OFFENSIVE LANGUAGE, SYMBOLS, OR THREATS TARGETING A PROTECTED
8 CLASS; AND
9 (V) DISTRIBUTION OF MATERIALS WITH MESSAGES USING
10 OFFENSIVE LANGUAGE, SYMBOLS, OR THREATS TARGETING A PROTECTED CLASS IN
11 A PUBLIC PLACE.
12 (B) (1) The Department shall collect, analyze, and disseminate:
13 (i) information about the incidence of crime in the State; and
14 (ii) information, including race and sex, on the total number of law
15 enforcement employees, de–identified and disaggregated by:
16 1. position for civilian employees; and
17 2. rank for sworn employees.
18 (2) Each law enforcement agency shall provide the Department with the
19 information described in paragraph (1) of this subsection in the format that the Secretary
20 requires.
21 [(b)] (C) (1) The Department shall collect and analyze information about
22 HATE CRIMES AND HATE BIAS incidents apparently directed against an individual or
23 group because of race, color, religious beliefs, sexual orientation, gender, disability, national
24 origin, or homelessness.
25 (2) Each local law enforcement agency and the State Fire Marshal shall
26 provide the Department with the information described in paragraph (1) of this subsection.
27 (3) The Department shall adopt procedures for the collection and analysis
28 of the information described in paragraph (1) of this subsection.
29 (4) The Department shall make quarterly reports to the Commission on
30 Civil Rights about the information described in paragraph (1) of this subsection.
31 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
32 October 1, 2025.

